                  </hi>. I am assistant to Messrs. Clay and Son, Cheapside. At a quarter past eight o'clock in the evening, on the 7th of April, I was in Gutter-lane—I felt a hand in my pocket—I turned, and saw the prisoner with my handkerchief in his hand—I took hold of him—he threw it away—I pulled him after me, and picked it up—this is it.</p>
